text: Room, bathroom and facilities are perfect for people like us who don’t spend much time in the room except for sleeping at night. Everything worked from the TV to the extra ventilator. Two sets of showers in bathroom as well! title: Best night's stay in London for this couple for many reasons.
text:
Top rating hygiene, compact but convenience I.e. Wall mounted soap/shampoo dispensers everything you need - wardrobe, hair dryer, kettle with tea, coffee sugar and milk supplies, fan, TV, safe. Staff super friendly and even though we couldn't check in early, we trusted them to put our bags in our room for us ready for when we'd returned later from our event. Staff at breakfast were friendly too. Cold drinks fridge in reception selling large bottles of water and various soft drinks  is a big win too! 
The surroundings were very quiet and peaceful and the location is FANTASTIC if you're planning a night/weekend in London with 3 tube stations within walking distance including access to the central line which runs 24 hrs!The only thing and I believe this has been mentioned before is the whole building in general seemed very warm. I only say this as a negative as in the summer months it's hard to regulate even though the window was opened. 
Plus there WAS a fan to use already in the room. 
I also am taking note of it being a big positive for in the winter. There's nothing worse than a cold room.

title: very nice stay with one really puzzling little eyesore
text: Nice hotel at a nice Notting Hill location, very quiet, very close to at least two different tube stations. Maybe a little pricey but I suspect this is London and hotels are expensive... Probably recently renovated, room in order with all appliances in working order. Some nice touches, such as multiple bedside outlets with USB outlets too. Wifi pretty good.A few details, which are really hard to reconcile with the overall good impression that a customer receives. Specifically, one that makes your eye sore is the elevator keyboard. Hard to describe in word, the keys are all broken and some are kept together with glue which sticks out of the key encasement, others have badly taped paper labels on them... unbelievable. Especially because the elevator looks rather new and modern. It does not make any sense that they don't have it immediately fixed, but the state of the whole keyboard is so degraded that this must have been going on for months. Since every single guest sees it and has to deal with it, if I were a manager I would fix it the next day. Instead... Manager: what are you waiting for? Luckily the room was in order and everything worked fine and looked rather new.

title: Calidad-precio bueno, Ubicacion muy buena.
text: Encontré el hotel bastante dificil, dando vueltas por.alli, pero puede ser que fue por culpa de mi google maps, que me sacó en otra calle y luego preguntando a otro hotel, me liaron mas.La ubicacion del hotel dentro de la ciudad es una muy,muy buena. Creo que es lo mejor que tiene este hotel.Cerca de metro, autobuses que me llevaron donde necesitaba, a solo 5kms de Buckingam Palace, perfecto para ir andando desde alli, traversando un parque enorme. A 1km del Market vintage que habia y a 2.5 Kms del centro comercial mas grande de Londres.El habitacion es pequeño, pero al final cumplió con mis espectativas de solo dormir por la noche y ya. El baño es muy pequeño, casi tienes que dejar la puerta abierta para poder hacer las cosas que necesitas.El habitacion esta ubicado abajo, al lado del comedor y de habitacion de las señoras de la limpieza. Al principio pensé que iba haber mucho ruido por las mañanas, pero no fue asi, las señoras que trabajaban en el comedor han sido muy silenciosas, casi no habia ruido. Tampoco desde la calle se escuchaba mucho.Tiene una tele muy grande para el tamaño del habitacion, con bastante programas, no lo he usado mucho. Tambien wifi con calidad 7.5-8.0/10, a veces se pierde la cobertura, pero dentro de 1min vuelve.Tambien tiene cafetera, secadora de pelo, un ventilador, telefono fijo- no he usado ninguno de estos para dar mas detalles.El desayuno es basico, se puede mejorar un poquito, hay solo dos tipos de queso, que se termina rapido y dos tipos de jamon cocido. Luego té, cafe, leche, cereales, zumo de naranjas y manzanas, pero no es natural. Y poco mas cosas. A mi no me gustó tanto, pero tampoco es muy malo. Un 6.0/10 lo valoraria.El personal de la recepcion puede intentar sonreir un poquito mas, me parecieron bastante frios, no te hablan si no hablas tu con ellos, no te preguntan proactivamente que tal estas, si te falta algo,etc.

The tap in the bathroom was extremely slow.  The toilet didn't flush properly.  The table in the bedroom was tiny and taken up with the coffee machine/coffee/tea/kettle. We would have mentioned the issues with the toilet to the staff when we checked-out but there was no one around at all and no way to contact anyone.  Just left our key on the reception desk.  Very strange hotel.

A very bad experience, be careful.

My single room was not as small as those I have found in comparable London hotels, and the bathroom was surprisingly roomy with excellent water pressure in the shower. The bed was comfortable, the television was of a good size, and the Wifi strength was excellent. Above all, the staff were extremely friendly and very helpful, happily lugging my largest case up to the first landing, which was not served by the elevator and repairing the television, which initially failed to work.The furniture in the room was not of good quality and some of it was broken. The carpet was clean but badly stained and the window would only open a crack, which would have been a serious problem in hotter weather. The continental breakfast was adequate but not distinguished and the use of stools for seating at the long central table (rather than the few tables around the sides, which had comfortable chairs) was unfortunate.

title: Very good location, clean rooms, good breakfast, friendly staff.
text: Breakfast was good. A little bit small variation of food, mostly sandwiches, boiled eggs and muesli and fruits but overall good. The room was very clean, bed was comfortable, the pillows not so much. we had one extra fold out bed in our room, for what purposes we have no idea but that didn't bother us. Toilet was also very clean. The Staff was very polite and helpful. Very big plus was that there were USB charging spots in the room so when traveling from other country you don't have to buy an extra adaptor for charging your devices. All the sightseeing are very close to the hotel, just a small walk through the Kensington and Hyde park.Out room was exactly next to the elevator so at night you could hear everybody who are coming up or going down with the elevator. You could also hear people talking when waiting their elevator. It was super hot days in London when we stayed. The room was extremely stuffy. Even opening the window didn't help. On our last night we didn't slept much because there was no air in the room, despite that the window was open. We had a van in the room, but it was making too much sound in the night that we could not use it. In the bathroom sink there was no pressure with the water, shower water pressure was good dough. Wifi connection was poor in the 5th floor where we stayed.Just a reminder. If you are traveling from Stansted airport and want to leave at night or a super early flight, don't count on the Bolt taxi or Uber because the taxi drivers don't like to drive so far at night and most likely are going to cancel on your request. Leave with airport bus or train. We just got super lucky that the Bolt driver was also traveling from that airport and picked us up in 2:30 am, otherwise we would have missed our flight.
